    {
      "check_id": "CWE-306",
      "path": "VulnerablePythonScript.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 37,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 37,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Missing Authentication on /unserialize Endpoint\n\nThe /unserialize endpoint accepts POST requests and deserializes arbitrary data using pickle without any authentication. Any unauthenticated user can send crafted pickle payloads to achieve remote code execution.\n\nImpact: Any anonymous user can achieve remote code execution on the server by sending a malicious pickle payload.\n\nFix: Add authentication checks to the /unserialize endpoint. Additionally, replace pickle deserialization with a safe serialization format like JSON.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-306"
          ],
          "finding_id": "446a69e5-47eb-4dde-b044-d82c04c0c10f"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-94",
      "path": "VulnerablePythonScript.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 33,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 33,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Insecure Deserialization via pickle.loads\n\nThe /unserialize endpoint deserializes untrusted user-supplied data using pickle.loads(). Python's pickle module can execute arbitrary code during deserialization, allowing an attacker to craft a malicious pickle payload that executes arbitrary system commands on the server.\n\nImpact: An attacker can achieve Remote Code Execution (RCE) by sending a crafted pickle payload, allowing full server compromise, data exfiltration, and lateral movement.\n\nFix: Never use pickle to deserialize untrusted data. Use safe serialization formats like JSON. If pickle is absolutely required, implement strict allowlisting of permitted classes using a custom Unpickler.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-94"
          ],
          "finding_id": "1c65d161-3c03-4d8b-972a-6c94ae07938c"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-312",
      "path": "VulnerablePythonScript.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 17,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 17,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Cleartext Storage of Password in Source Code\n\nThe password 'password123' is stored in cleartext in the source code variable PASSWORD. This is a cleartext storage of sensitive information issue separate from the hardcoding concern \u2014 the password is never hashed or encrypted.\n\nImpact: The plaintext password is exposed to anyone who can read the source code, version control history, or backups. It cannot be revoked without changing the source code.\n\nFix: Never store passwords in plaintext. Use a proper password hashing algorithm (bcrypt, argon2) and store hashes in a database. Retrieve secrets from environment variables or a secrets manager.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-312"
          ],
          "finding_id": "2255b276-a6e4-402f-bb0d-9019702fc7cc"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-307",
      "path": "VulnerablePythonScript.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 19,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 19,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Missing Authentication on /login Endpoint (No Rate Limiting)\n\nThe /login endpoint accepts POST requests for authentication but has no rate limiting or account lockout mechanism. Combined with hardcoded credentials, this allows unlimited brute-force attempts.\n\nImpact: An attacker can perform unlimited brute-force login attempts to guess the hardcoded credentials.\n\nFix: Implement rate limiting on the login endpoint (e.g., using Flask-Limiter) and add account lockout after repeated failed attempts.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-307"
          ],
          "finding_id": "c67317ea-8fe7-45fd-a866-392fde32febb"
        }
      }
